Terese places the seed in a small pot of earth, and sings lovingly. A sweet smell fills the air, and the soil glows softly. Suddenly, eight plants burst forth from the dirt! Terese blinks in disbelief.
Wow. I sure didn't expect that.
Terese places the seed in a small pot of earth, and speaks soothingly. A acrid smell fills the air, as a dark plant springs forth!
How beautiful! And how rare! Please take good care of this...it would be a shame if anything happened to such a wondrous living thing!
Terese places the seed in a small pot of earth, and speaks soothingly. A acrid smell fills the air, as a dark plant springs forth!
How beautiful! And how rare! Please take good care of this... it would be a shame if anything happened to such a wondrous living thing!
What do you want? Wasting my time, no doubt, wasting my time! Don't you have some grandiose quest to do, or innocent monkeys to kill? Leave me alone with my plants. Growing them isn't easy, you know.
If I really believed you cared, I might help you grow your own plants. But I'm sure you wouldn't find them to be terribly "elite".

Yes, the Shreth have been eating the plants. That's part of Dereth's new ecology. Go look it up. But, if you happen to go rooting through Shreth droppings, as I imagine you like to do, I'll take any seeds that you might find.
Do you see all these lovely new plants? I woke up one morning and their fronds had appeared out of nowhere! Even an animal-killer such as you cannot dampen my spirits.
